    <h1>FC08: User Access Request</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"FC08:UserAccessRequest-1.AccessRequestfornewApplicationAc=
count">1. Access Request for new Application Account</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Assumption for this process is that users do not have an account in the =
application for which access is being requested.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Request for access is raised by the requester either on behalf of anothe=
r user or for self by providing the required information in the User access=
 request form.</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IdentityIQ check for SOD violation, if an SOD violation exists=
 then the request will not be submitted. If no violation occurs the request=
 gets submitted.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The request is sent to the requestee=E2=80=99s line manager for approval=
. If the request is rejected by the line manager, the requester is notified=
 by email and the request is automatically closed.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>If the request is approved by the line manager, the request is sent to t=
he access owner for the next level of approval. If the request is rejected =
by the access owner, the requester is notified, and the request is automati=
cally closed.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once approved by the access owner, the request will be sent for provisio=
ning.</p></li>
<li>
<p>After receiving the required approvals, access is provisioned as defined=
 by the application and the requester is notified.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>The security team will be notified by a ServiceNow ticket if there is a =
problem encountered during the request provisioning. The security team will=
 analyze the request status and take appropriate action to resolve issues e=
ither by provisioning the access manually or by creating a new request in S=
ailPoint IIQ to retry the access provisioning.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>New access requests created by the security team for provisioning retry =
will follow the same path as a new access request.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Dependency:</strong></p>
<p>Table-14</p>
