<h3 id=3D"FC08:UserAccessRequest-2.RequestforAccessProvisioning/De-Provisio=
ningforanExistingApplicationAccount">2. Request for Access Provisioning/De-=
Provisioning for an Existing Application Account</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Assumption for this process is that users already have an account in the=
 application for which additional access is being requested or existing acc=
ess is being removed.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Request for additional access or removal for existing access is raised b=
y the requester either on behalf of another user or for self by providing r=
equired information in user access request form.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>SailPoint IIQ check for SOD violation, if an SOD violation exists then t=
he request will not be submitted. If no violation occurs the request gets s=
ubmitted.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The request is sent to the requestee=E2=80=99s line manager for approval=
. If the request is rejected by the line manager, the requester is notified=
 by email and the requests are automatically closed.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>If the request is approved by the line manager, the request is sent to t=
he access owner for the next level of approval. If the request is rejected =
by the access owner, the requester is notified, and the request is automati=
cally closed.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once approved by the access owner, the request will be sent for provisio=
ning/de-provisioning.</p></li>
<li>
<p>After receiving the required approvals, access is provisioned/de-provisi=
oned as defined by the application and the requester is notified.&nbsp;</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>The security team will be notified by a ServiceNow ticket if there is a =
problem encountered during the request provisioning. The security team will=
 analyze the request status and take appropriate action to resolve the issu=
e either by provisioning/de-provisioning the access manually or by creating=
 a new request in SailPoint IIQ to re-try the access provisioning/de-provis=
ioning.&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>New access requests created by the security team for provisioning/de-pro=
visioning retry will follow the same path as a new access request.</p></li>
</ul>
